## Quick Start

```bash
mise install
mise run install
mise run install-hooks
mise run lint
mise run test
```

`uv.lock` is created during the first dependency sync. Commit it with the
project so CI and local installs use the same resolved dependencies. The sync
installs this project as well as its dependencies. `mise install` installs the
pinned cross-language CLI tools; uv alone provisions the Python selected by
`.python-version` when `mise run install` performs the first sync.

uv uses managed Python builds only. Exact patch choices are expert mode: if the
pinned uv release cannot provide the recorded patch on the current platform,
choose another exact patch or a supported minor. There is no hidden system or
source-build fallback.

## Commands

- `mise run install`: install this package and its dependencies.
- `mise run lint-fast`: run edit-safe lint targets for active development.
- `mise run lint`: run the full lint gate used by CI.
- `mise run lint-full`: explicit name for the full lint gate.
- `mise run format`: apply Ruff formatting and autofixes for Python files under
  `src` and `tests`, then format TOML files with Taplo.
- `mise run test`: run the pytest suite under `tests`.
- `mise run test-cov`: run the pytest suite with a coverage report.
- `mise run install-hooks`: install prek-managed pre-commit and pre-push hooks.

## Docker

```bash
docker build -t {{ project_name }} .
```

The image keeps a framework-neutral smoke command. Replace it only when the
project chooses its real application runtime. The image uses the same
uv-managed `.python-version` interpreter as local development and CI.
{% if use_github_actions %}

## CI

GitHub Actions runs `mise run lint` and `mise run test-cov`. Commit `uv.lock`
after the first local sync before relying on CI.
{% endif %}

